race.comment: Tricky with some, and the race day betting will be instructive. RUTHVEN RUSH (1) resumes and three back was narrowly beaten at Eagle Farm on debut. Owns a trial win on the inner track and will be naturally improved. On what we've seen, he will take beating. BENT BRIDGE (14) looked good early doors and resumed again here two weeks ago, beaten 2.6L when expected to need it. Will have taken improvement and no surprise if he's right in the finish. Draws awkwardly, but he's likely to race boldly. ENTERPRISE KHAN (5) is third up and showed enough at Ipswich fresh to say he's a chance. Has an inside gate and 3kig claim and the blinkers are on again. HOWDOYOUZOU (2) debuts for the Webster yard and his trials have been sharp.  GYPSY JOY (7) debuts for the Nolen yard and trialled well enough to keep onside.
